ystic ovary syndrome","Sheehan syndrome"],"correctOptions":[4],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EThis patient\u0027s presentation of\u003Cstrong\u003E \u003C/strong\u003Esix months of anovulation after a complicated childbirth is typical of \u003Cstrong\u003ESheehan syndrome.\u003C/strong\u003E This occurs when severe postpartum haemorrhage causes pituitary infarction and subsequent hypopituitarism. The resulting loss of follicle-stimulating hormone (FSH) and luteinising hormone (LH) leads to anovulation and amenorrhoea.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EAnorexia nervosa\u003C/strong\u003E and \u003Cstrong\u003Eexcessive exercise\u003C/strong\u003E cause functional hypothalamic amenorrhoea through suppression of gonadotropin-releasing hormone (GnRH). \u003Cstrong\u003EKallmann syndrome\u003C/strong\u003E is a congenital condition causing hypogonadotropic hypogonadism due to failed GnRH neuron migration. \u003Cstrong\u003EPolycystic ovary syndrome\u003C/strong\u003E is an ovarian disorder characterised by hyperandrogenism and irregular ovulation.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":["","","","",""],"learningPoints":["Sheehan syndrome is postpartum pituitary necrosis causing hypopituitarism and anovulation","Pituitary disorders causing anovulation are distinguished from hypothalamic and peripheral causes"],"references":["Melmed, S., Polonsky, K. S., Larsen, P. R., \u0026 Kronenberg, H. M. (2015). Williams textbook of endocrinology E-Book. Elsevier Health Sciences","Clark, O. H., Duh, Q. Y., Kebebew, E., Gosnell, J. E., \u0026 Shen, W. T. (Eds.). (2016). Textbook of endocrine surgery. JP Medical Ltd","Young, W. F. (2011). Netter\u0027s Endocrine System: Netter Collection of Medical Illustrations: Endocrine System E-book. Elsevier Health Sciences","Wass, J. A., \u0026 Stewart, P. M. (Eds.). (2011). Oxford textbook of endocrinology and diabetes. Oxford University Press, USA."]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","i